<item>
            <title>[HIVE-10781] HadoopJobExecHelper Leaks RunningJobs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-10781</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On one of our busy hadoop cluster, hiveServer2 holds more than 4000 org.apache.hadoop.mapred.JobClient$NetworkedJob instances,while only has less than 3 backgroud handler thread at the same time.&lt;br/&gt;
All these instances are hold in one LinkedList from org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.exec.mr.HadoopJobExecHelper&apos;s  runningJobs property,which is static.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12831637">HIVE-10781</key>
            <summary>HadoopJobExecHelper Leaks RunningJobs</summary>
